KwaZulu-Natal police have arrested 39 suspects for allegedly dealing in drugs. Police targeted suspected drug dealers at Chatsworth, Phoenix, Pietermaritzburg and Madadeni, where their premises were searched and large amounts of drugs were seized. Police also shut down four illegal outlets. KwaZulu-Natal Police Spokesperson, Thembeka Mbele says all arrested suspects will appear in various courts in the province. “Police officers are also targeting liquor outlets.They have closed down four liquor outlets. Four suspects were charged in dealing in liquor without a licence,” explains Mbele. 